notesStmt.note: This Missal was created for Benedictine use in a church dedicated to Ambrose in the province of Ravenna, perhaps S. Ambrosii de Rancla (Ranchio) near Sarsina. The manuscript, which dates to the eleventh century, is striking for its two crucifixion images, one on fol. 7r, and another, drawn only in pen, on fol. 9r. Early musical notation in the form of neumes also appear throughout.

msContents.textLang: The primary language in this manuscript is Latin.

decoDesc.decoNote: Two full-page miniatures of the crucifixion, one in color and one only in ink; incipit page in silver and gold; occasional vegetal initials in ink (e.g. fol. 6v); rubrics in red; text in brown ink
